- An approach to the provision of information to management to assist strategic policy, **formulation** and **achievement**.
- Emphasises the need to provide the user with a set of information which addresses all **relevant areas of performance** in an objective and unbiased fashion
- The information provided may include both **financial and non-financial elements** and cover areas such as **profitability, customer satisfaction, internal efficiency and innovation.**
- Takes a strategic holisitic view of the organisation including all departments of the organisation and for each of the previously mentioned perspectives, goals and measures are defined and progress is monitored to ensure full implementation of the strategy. 
- Very much related to [[Budgeting|Budgeting]] as one of the major tools to translate strategic goals into financial plans
- Where ratios provide means to analyse financial performance in various different ways, BS adds perspective of other aspects to the performance of an organisation which can only be evaluated by looking at specific indicators that go beyond the financial indicators 
	- e.g. Client satisfaction, number of clients, number of employees, 
	- Purpose is to **support strategic decision making**
	- BS is an approach whereby strategic performance of an organisation is looked at from at least 4 aspects
		- Customer satisfaction
		- Efficency 
		- Ability to improve company's performance
		- Financial performance
- What is interesting is that you cannot directly act on the financial performance, only the other 3 can have an effect on financial performance. If you want to increase revenue, you need to improve customer satisfaction, quality, percieved value, efficiency of operations (cost optimisation). You can take decisions on specific operations and leverage them to improve financial performance
- Addresses the limitations of financial measures (e.g. the financial statements) - since 90s most valuable assets of a company are non financial (people, customer relationships, innovation). Intangible assets play a central role in value creation - if companies want to improve management of their intangible assets, have to integrate the measurement of intangible assets into management systems. 
- Concept is now a **management tool for describing, communicating and implementing strategy**
- If you don't measure something, you can't improve it - ie. manage it - if we don't measure most important aspects, how can we manage it?

## Managing strategy with BS
- Tries to translate various perspective from strategy to objectives with measures, targets and initiatives (on each measure - learning and growth, efficiency, customer satisfaction)
- Indicators for financial information are primarily those for ratio analysis 
![Pasted image 20220408115732.png](data:image/png;base64,)
![Pasted image 20220408120036.png](data:image/png;base64,)
- How does this link with [[Budgeting|Budgeting]]? (or what does it have to do with accounting other than the Financial section)
- Each indicator implies resources manager should use to reach the targets, represented as a budget. BS therefore supports creation of a budget.
